1
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,119
You're not sleeping well, right?

2
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:56,679
No.

3
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:57,920
Are you okay?

4
00:00:58,039 --> 00:00:59,359
I slept until dawn.

5
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,359
Sleeping too much can also lead to dampness.

6
00:01:10,079 --> 00:01:10,959
I'll give you a medicine bag.

7
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:18,560
Carry it with you.

8
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,799
I'll follow your advice.

9
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:33,439
Dear engineer,

10
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,040
why have you graced my humble place today?

11
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:38,519
Is it because you can't understand the drawings

12
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,760
and come to me for inspiration?

13
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,799
My clinic is open to the public.

14
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:43,480
What?

15
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:44,719
Can't I come here?

16
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:45,640
You should have come earlier.

17
00:01:45,879 --> 00:01:47,000
Look at your complexion,

18
00:01:47,159 --> 00:01:48,920
pale and dark,

19
00:01:49,439 --> 00:01:51,159
signs of severe kidney deficiency.

20
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,840
Nonsense.

21
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,040
I get annual check-ups.

22
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,319
I'm in great shape.

23
00:01:55,719 --> 00:01:57,319
Isn't it unnecessary for someone

24
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,680
in such good health to come here?

25
00:01:59,319 --> 00:01:59,840
I...

26
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:00,920
Just passing by.

27
00:02:01,599 --> 00:02:03,959
I'm here to discuss something with Professor Du.

28
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,560
You sure know how to drop by.

29
00:02:13,039 --> 00:02:13,680
Professor Du,

30
00:02:13,919 --> 00:02:16,439
I've been tending this clivia for days, but it's not thriving.

31
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:19,280
You're an expert; could you take a look?

32
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:23,159
The soil is new,

33
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,599
and the fertilizer is sufficient.

34
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:26,360
How did it end up like this?

35
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,280
The roots need a breath of life.

36
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,240
Your focus

37
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,479
on the flowers,

38
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,319
how can they thrive?

39
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,439
Do you even know

40
00:02:37,599 --> 00:02:38,479
how to take care of flowers?

41
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,680
Back in the day, Professor Du and I

42
00:02:40,759 --> 00:02:42,240
had a balcony full of flowers.

43
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,039
Professor Du knows flowers best.

44
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,439
This flower

45
00:02:59,319 --> 00:03:00,639
has a classic case of lovesickness.

46
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,800
The roots aren't rotten,

47
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,360
it's just

48
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,719
not getting the care it needs.

49
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,080
Professor Du,

50
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:17,240
why don't you take this flower back

51
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,879
and try to save it?

52
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:19,719
Later,

53
00:03:19,919 --> 00:03:21,360
I'll come to your place to learn,

54
00:03:21,439 --> 00:03:21,919
okay?

55
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:22,879
No need to go to that much trouble.

56
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,879
Herbs and flowers share the same origin.

57
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,000
Don't worry,

58
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:27,680
I'll take better care of it than you.

59
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,080
What does it have to do with you?

60
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:39,240
The roots have been cut.

61
00:03:39,599 --> 00:03:40,719
No wonder it's wilting.

62
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,639
Mr. Engineer,

63
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,080
you've got quite the green thumb, huh?

64
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,439
You've put in a lot of effort.

65
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,280
You shouldn't have cut the root.

66
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,240
If you really want to join,

67
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,560
the three of us can go watch a movie.

68
00:04:01,719 --> 00:04:02,240
Go.

69
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:03,960
Who wants to go with you?

70
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:08,960
Whose car is blocking the entrance?

71
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:10,280
It needs to be moved.

72
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,520
A car from someone who shouldn't have been passing by.

73
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:16,480
Go, go, go.

74
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,160
Go.

75
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:20,399
Fortunately,

76
00:04:20,439 --> 00:04:21,800
this branch wasn't cut all the way through.

77
00:04:22,519 --> 00:04:23,240
It can recover.

78
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:24,879
Come on.

79
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,319
You've driven him away.

80
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:28,079
Are you really going to help him take care of the flowers?

81
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:29,720
I must take good care of them.

82
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:31,279
Otherwise, someone

83
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,680
will keep finding excuses to see you.

84
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:36,519
Cuckoo.

85
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:37,839
I'll go deal with it.

86
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:41,800
Pleasing.

87
00:04:42,319 --> 00:04:43,480
So pleasing.

88
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:23,079
Mom,

89
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,279
what's wrong with you?

90
00:05:24,959 --> 00:05:26,639
Nothing, I'm fine.

91
00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:29,079
I'm going to dance.

92
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,360
Dance?

93
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,399
Dance with Uncle Lan?

94
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,040
Who asked him out?

95
00:05:34,319 --> 00:05:35,000
Let me tell you,

96
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,920
don't mention Lan Jianhua in front of me anymore.

97
00:05:37,439 --> 00:05:38,839
There are plenty of fish in the sea.

98
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:39,959
I broke up

99
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,000
with him.

100
00:05:42,439 --> 00:05:43,040
You broke up with him?

101
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:51,759
Doctor Lan,

102
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:53,439
are you single?

103
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,040
If you are, let's be partners.

104
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,639
Ma'am, I'm not single.

105
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:58,160
My Cuckoo will be here soon.

106
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,360
Alright then.

107
00:05:59,439 --> 00:06:00,240
Next time.

108
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:00,839
Okay.

109
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,439
Okay.

110
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,040
Cuckoo, you're here.

111
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,399
You're here.

112
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:15,399
I'm not too late, am I?

113
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:16,480
I just got here too.

114
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:21,319
Cuckoo.

115
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:23,000
Aren't we supposed to dance together?

116
00:06:23,639 --> 00:06:24,519
I forgot about you.

117
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:29,800
Delete.

118
00:06:30,399 --> 00:06:31,439
Delete, don't contact me anymore.

119
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,279
We're done.

120
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,160
Done.

121
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,160
Juan.

122
00:06:39,519 --> 00:06:40,000
No.

123
00:06:49,319 --> 00:06:50,000
Sorry, it's fine.

124
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:50,519
Go on.

125
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,279
Juan.

126
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:54,319
Juan.

127
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,360
What's wrong, Juan?

128
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:56,920
Go away.

129
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:03,800
Why did you break up suddenly?

130
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,720
Weren't you fine yesterday?

131
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:08,279
What did your mom say to you?

132
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:09,879
Nothing.

133
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:11,839
She just told me

134
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,240
that they broke up.

135
00:07:19,199 --> 00:07:20,680
They broke up?

136
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,319
Then

137
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,079
we don't have to

138
00:07:28,839 --> 00:07:30,360
be brother and sister anymore.

139
00:07:32,399 --> 00:07:33,480
We don't have to meet anymore.

140
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,360
Are you happy?

141
00:07:45,279 --> 00:07:46,199
Is it that obvious?

142
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:53,920
Don't worry.

143
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:55,800
I won't let you have your way.

144
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,360
The pulse is floating and rapid.

145
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:17,920
and the pulse at the cun position is deep and sluggish.

146
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:19,199
The liver Qi is stagnated,

147
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,680
causing heartache.

148
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:25,120
A single acupuncture treatment will cure everything.

149
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:26,800
My girl,

150
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,879
what are you doing?

151
00:08:30,639 --> 00:08:31,879
I'm saving lives and healing the wounded.

152
00:08:32,759 --> 00:08:33,799
If you keep being so listless,

153
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,320
Auntie Dujuan will like you even less.

154
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:37,440
Mom,

155
00:08:38,279 --> 00:08:39,320
if you can't let go,

156
00:08:39,879 --> 00:08:41,559
I'll go to the clinic and check on Uncle Lan.

157
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:43,840
No need.

158
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,360
Who can't let go?

159
00:08:45,759 --> 00:08:46,720
You don't have to go to the hospital.

160
00:08:47,279 --> 00:08:48,080
You don't need to go at all.

161
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:49,240
Come on.

162
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,600
Cheer up.

163
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:51,879
When it comes to heartbreak,

164
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,720
it's all about putting on a brave face.

165
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:55,799
Smile.

166
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,279
I'll post a WeChat Moment for you.

167
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:05,480
Will it work?

168
00:09:06,559 --> 00:09:07,200
Just watch.

169
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,799
Embrace the new life.

170
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,519
He's doing quite well.

171
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:17,919
Son,

172
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:19,320
take a photo for me.

173
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,799
The caption should be,

174
00:09:21,399 --> 00:09:22,360
"Life is peaceful."

175
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,720
Out with the old, in with the new.

176
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:30,679
Dad,

177
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:32,919
why did you

178
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,519
suddenly move this?

179
00:09:35,039 --> 00:09:35,600
Why?

180
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:39,360
Your photo trick doesn't work at all.

181
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:41,519
I'm Pisces, she's Aquarius.

182
00:09:41,639 --> 00:09:42,440
The internet says

183
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,320
I'm water, she's air.

184
00:09:44,679 --> 00:09:47,039
The old layout blocked the air,

185
00:09:48,279 --> 00:09:49,000
creating

186
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,360
a stagnant situation.

187
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,919
Dad, this won't work.

188
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:55,200
You're changing the subject.

189
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,200
Sit down.

190
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:04,320
- ♪How much do I love you♪ - Mom, mom.

191
00:10:04,399 --> 00:10:05,360
Be careful.

192
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:06,799
Stop drinking.

193
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,360
Wasn't it you who dumped her?

194
00:10:08,639 --> 00:10:10,559
Dumping someone hurts more.

195
00:10:11,559 --> 00:10:13,480
My happiness was all an act.

196
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:15,000
I've come to realize,

197
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,480
why would I lie to myself like this?

198
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,639
I just love her.

199
00:10:19,159 --> 00:10:20,159
I just like her.

200
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,519
And now she's suddenly dumped me.

201
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,240
Xiaochuan,

202
00:10:23,639 --> 00:10:25,919
have you ever felt suddenly dumped?

203
00:10:32,039 --> 00:10:34,600
The one who breaks up is the sadder one.

204
00:10:35,159 --> 00:10:36,279
You don't understand.

205
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:38,039
It's useless to tell you.

206
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:39,639
I won't talk about it.

207
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:42,440
♪My heart is cold.♪

208
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:53,600
♪A gentle kiss♪

209
00:10:55,320 --> 00:11:00,879
♪has moved my heart.♪

210
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:32,519
What are you doing here?
